about.contributorsSubtitle.value: We're grateful to the talented developers and engineers who have contributed their time and expertise to make YourDigitalRights.org better for everyone.

about.founder2Role.value: Design Consultant and Visiting Lecturer at UCL and UAL

about.foundersSubtitle.value: YourDigitalRights.org was founded by two passionate advocates for digital rights and human-centered design.

about.globalText.value: We support 25+ data protection laws, covering more than four billion people, and our platform is available in multiple languages thanks to a growing volunteer community.

about.heroSubtitle.value: YourDigitalRights.org is a free, open-source service that helps people take back control of their online privacy. We make it simple to exercise your legal rights over your personal data — to ask companies to delete it, access it, or stop selling it — under privacy laws like the GDPR, CCPA, and dozens more around the world.

about.heroTitle.value: Taking Back Control of Your Personal Data

about.introText.value: With just a few clicks, you can find thousands of companies that hold your data and send them a legally-binding request. Our built-in follow-up system keeps track of your requests and helps you escalate cases to the right regulator when organizations fail to comply.

about.newDescription.value: YourDigitalRights.org is a free, open-source service that helps people take back control of their online privacy.

about.openSourceText.value: All code, data, and methods are public and free to reuse.

about.privacyFirstText.value: We collect no personal data by default, run no ads, and never sell user information.

about.stat1Text.value: Data requests submitted to organizations worldwide

about.supportText.value: From sending your first request to filing a complaint with a regulator, our tools help you every step of the way.

about.whyWeExistText1.value: The internet was built for people — but today, most of it is powered by the trade in our personal information. We believe everyone deserves digital privacy by default, not just by law. YourDigitalRights.org was created to make those rights practical, simple, and enforceable.

about.whyWeExistText2.value: , a nonprofit organization advancing digital human rights worldwide. Together, we build open, people-centered tools that empower individuals — not corporations or governments — to be first-class citizens in the digital world.

donate.closing.subtitle.value: Your support keeps YourDigitalRights.org free, open, and independent. Whether it's €5 or €500, every donation makes a difference.

donate.closing.thanks.value: Thank you for standing up for privacy and empowering people everywhere.

donate.intro.paragraph1.value: YourDigitalRights.org is a free, open-source service that helps people reclaim their privacy online. It is maintained by Conscious Digital, a nonprofit organization building people-centered digital initiatives to advance digital human rights.

donate.intro.paragraph2.value: We do not show ads, sell data, or rely on invasive tech. Instead, we rely on the support of a global community. Your donation directly powers the tools that let people everywhere request their data, delete their profiles, and stand up to surveillance.
